	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">S.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Conditio mea talis <placeName ref="place97">Basileae</placeName> fuit, quemadmodum iamdudum scripsi<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Oben <ref target="file11265">Nr. 1222</ref>.</note>, ut inde mensam haberem et 24 florenos.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Sed quoniam discipuli omnes<note xml:id="fna" type="footnote" n="a">vor omnes <hi>gestrichenes</hi> fere.</note> ex paedagogio<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2"><persName ref="person238">Werdmüller</persName> war Lehrer am Pädagogium (s. HBBW VIII <ref target="file11189">[Nr. 1146]</ref>, S. 170, Anm. 5).</note> pestem fugerunt, redeunt nulli, haud immerito mensa denegatur, quae non ob aliam causam antea dabatur, quam ut praelegerem in Offitiis<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3"><persName ref="person632">Cicero</persName>, De officiis (vgl. dazu oben <ref target="file11265">Nr. 1222</ref>, 9-11).</note> et a coena repeterem.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Soli remanserunt 24 floreni, propter quos in <persName ref="person1155">Herodiano</persName><note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Gemeint ist <persName ref="person1155">Herodians</persName> Kaisergeschichte (s. ebd.).</note> pergo; et quia per annum mihi non sufficiunt 24 floreni (nam inde ne mensam quidem emo, tantum abest, ut reliqua necessaria comparari queant), commodissime tuas literas<note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5">Nicht erhalten.</note> nuper accipiebam de me in d. Rellicani<note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6">Offenbar war erwogen worden, <persName ref="person175">Rhellikan</persName> als Zuchtmeister des Fraumünster-Alumnats durch <persName ref="person238">Werdmüller</persName> zu ersetzen.</note> locum.</s>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quamvis autem nihil certi affirmabas, tamen interea temporis hic <placeName ref="place97">Basileae</placeName> non aliam conditionem ambivi existimans indecorum esse conditionem<pb type="edition" next="148"/> iamiam deserendam vel petere vel offerre.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quodsi igitur nondum est occasio domum redeundi, nihil aliud abs te et ab reliquis peto collegiarchis<note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7">Die weiteren Schulverordneten sind nicht bekannt.</note>, quam ut vel pauci anni concedantur, quibus aliquod munus sustineam, ne maiores faciam sumptus.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Plus satis offendi patrem<note xml:id="fn8" type="footnote" n="8"><persName ref="person2472">Heinrich Werdmüller</persName>.</note> magnitudine debitorum, et merito nec ipse largitur amplius nec <persName ref="person891">Froschouerus</persName> diutius expectat, ideoque vehementer oro tuam humanitatem, ne graveris obedientissimo filio tuo per proximum nuntium, quid optimum visum fuerit, significare.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vale, charissime pater, cum uxore<note xml:id="fn9" type="footnote" n="9">Anna, geb. Adlischwyler.</note> et liberis<note xml:id="fn10" type="footnote" n="10">Siehe oben <ref target="file11260">Nr. 1217</ref>, Anm. 46. - Am Tag nach der Abfassung des vorliegenden Briefes kam <persName ref="person562">Johannes Bullinger</persName> zur Welt (vgl. unten <ref target="file11320">Nr. 1277</ref>, Anm. 17).</note>.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><placeName ref="place97">Basileae</placeName>, 23. maii 1539.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><persName ref="person238">Otho Werdmüllerus</persName> tibi deditissimus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Clarissimo viro domino Henrico Bullingero, patri suo plurimum colendo.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tiguri.</s>
				</p>
